body:
Looks like something is special about the environment...
I've tried to repro but service runs fine in my case:
Code:
```
        public void Start(string[] startupArguments, ServiceStoppedCallback serviceStoppedCallback)
        {
            try
            {
                using (var ps = PowerShell.Create())
                {
                    foreach (var result in ps.AddScript("$PID; \"$($PSVersionTable.PSVersion) $($PSVersionTable.PSEdition)\"").Invoke())
                    {
                        Debug.WriteLine(result.ToString());
                    }
                }
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {
                Debug.WriteLine(ex);
                throw;
            }
        }
```
when stepped through in VS 2017 debugger prints this in output window:
```
6660
6.0.0 Core
```
and service is displayed as running:
```
PS C:\WINDOWS\system32> Get-Service PowerShellCoreService

Status   Name               DisplayName
------   ----               -----------
Running  PowerShellCoreS... PowerShellCoreService
```

My env is:
```
Windows Server x64 / 16299.0.amd64fre.rs3_release.170922-1354
VS 2017 Community 15.4.0
Microsoft (R) Build Engine version 15.4.8.50001 for .NET Core
dotnet --version == 2.0.2
```
